Former Chelsea star, Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink, has named Arsenal’s Bukayo Saka, as his Player of the Season. Hasselbaink said that Saka has done well for Arsenal this season. According to him, nothing fazes the England international, who has scored 10 goals and registered nine assists for the Gunners so far this season. “Bukayo for me is player of the season,” Hasselbaink was quoted by Daily Mail UK as saying. “He has done so well. He’s been getting better and better and taking responsibility, popping up in important moments. “Nothing fazes him, and for me, player of the season.”